<body>
    <div class="header">
        <h1>Privacy Policy for BandHouse</h1>
        <p class="last-updated"><strong>Last Updated:</strong> October 22, 2025</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Introduction</h2>
        <p>BandHouse ("we," "our," or "us") respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal data. This privacy policy explains how we collect, use, and share information when you use our mobile application.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
        
        <h3>Information You Provide</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> Name, email address, password</li>
            <li><strong>Profile Information:</strong> User type (Viewer, Band, Host), profile picture (optional)</li>
            <li><strong>Event Content:</strong> Event flyers, venue information, dates, times, ticket links</li>
            <li><strong>Social Links:</strong> Instagram handles and Spotify links (optional)</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Information We Collect Automatically</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Location Data:</strong> We collect your device's location to show nearby events and calculate distances</li>
            <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> App interactions, features used, events viewed</li>
            <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> Device type, operating system version, unique device identifiers</li>
            <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> Firebase Analytics data to improve app performance</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use the collected information to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Provide and maintain the BandHouse service</li>
            <li>Show you nearby events based on your location</li>
            <li>Enable you to post and discover music events</li>
            <li>Connect bands with venues and music fans</li>
            <li>Send notifications about events (with your permission)</li>
            <li>Improve app performance and user experience</li>
            <li>Prevent fraud and abuse</li>
            <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
        
        <h3>We Share Data With:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Google Maps/Places:</strong> To display maps and autocomplete addresses</li>
            <li><strong>Firebase (Google):</strong> For authentication, database, and analytics</li>
            <li><strong>Other Users:</strong> Your posted events and public profile information are visible to other app users</li>
            <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> Third-party services that help us operate the app</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>We Do NOT:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Sell your personal information to third parties</li>
            <li>Share your email or password with anyone</li>
            <li>Use your location data for purposes other than showing nearby events</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Your Rights and Choices</h2>
        
        <h3>You Can:</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Access:</strong> View all your posted events in your profile</li>
            <li><strong>Edit:</strong> Update or delete your posted events</li>
            <li><strong>Delete Account:</strong> Contact us to delete your account and data</li>
            <li><strong>Opt-Out:</strong> Disable location services (may limit app functionality)</li>
            <li><strong>Export:</strong> Request a copy of your data</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Location Services</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>You can enable/disable location access in iOS Settings</li>
            <li>Without location access, distance filtering will not work</li>
            <li>We only access your location when you use the app (not in background)</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Data Security</h2>
        <p>We implement appropriate security measures including:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Firebase Authentication with encrypted passwords</li>
            <li>Secure HTTPS connections for all data transmission</li>
            <li>Firebase App Check to prevent abuse</li>
            <li>Regular security updates</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>BandHouse is not intended for users under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect data from children under 13. If you believe we have collected data from a child, please contact us immediately.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Data Retention</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Account Data:</strong> Retained while your account is active</li>
            <li><strong>Posted Events:</strong> Retained until you delete them or your account</li>
            <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> Anonymized analytics data may be retained indefinitely</li>
            <li><strong>Deleted Data:</strong> Removed within 30 days of account deletion</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>BandHouse uses the following third-party services:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Firebase (Google):</strong> Authentication, database, analytics
                <br><a href="https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy" target="_blank">Privacy Policy</a>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Google Maps API:</strong> Location and mapping services
                <br><a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank">Privacy Policy</a>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this privacy policy from time to time. We will notify you of significant changes by:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Updating the "Last Updated" date</li>
            <li>Sending an in-app notification</li>
            <li>Posting a notice in the app</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Content Moderation</h2>
        <p>BandHouse allows users to post event flyers and other content. We take user safety seriously:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Users can report inappropriate content using the in-app report button</li>
            <li>We review all reports and remove content that violates our guidelines</li>
            <li>Repeat violators may have their accounts suspended or terminated</li>
            <li>We cooperate with law enforcement when required by law</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section contact-box">
        <h2>Contact Us</h2>
        <p>If you have questions about this privacy policy or our data practices, contact us at:</p>
        <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:BandHouseHelp@gmail.com">BandHouseHelp@gmail.com</a></p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Your Consent</h2>
        <p>By using BandHouse, you consent to this privacy policy and our collection and use of information as described.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>California Privacy Rights (CCPA)</h2>
        <p>If you are a California resident, you have additional rights:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Right to know what personal information we collect</li>
            <li>Right to delete your personal information</li>
            <li>Right to opt-out of sale of personal information (we don't sell data)</li>
            <li>Right to non-discrimination for exercising your rights</li>
        </ul>
        <p>To exercise these rights, contact us at the email above.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>GDPR Rights (European Users)</h2>
        <p>If you are in the EU/EEA, you have rights under GDPR:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Right of access to your data</li>
            <li>Right to rectification (correction)</li>
            <li>Right to erasure ("right to be forgotten")</li>
            <li>Right to restrict processing</li>
            <li>Right to data portability</li>
            <li>Right to object to processing</li>
        </ul>
        <p>To exercise these rights, contact us at the email above.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section" style="margin-top: 60px; padding-top: 20px; border-top: 2px solid #eee; text-align: center; color: #999;">
